715608f.text:
West 137th Street, south side, between Lenox and Fifth Aves., showing the south wall of the 4-story ambulance station unit of Harlem Hospital, after the dismantlement of a 4-story glass veranda, which was attached to the building. The work was carried out with W.P.A. labor and funds.
February 4, 1937.
W.P.A. Photo.
City Wide Project.

715609f-a.text: West 137th Street, south side, between Lenox and Fifth Aves., showing the 4-story ambulance station unit of Harlem Hospital, as seen from the interior ambulance driveway and yard.  January 6, 1937.  W.P.A. Photo.  City Wide Project.
